<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Q</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-22 18:24:57</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>No, the only thing that must be evaluated when selling an item is: What will people pay you for it?<BR>
<BR>
Now, let's say it's a rare thing like this, and it's the best you can get.  That means that if you're selling it at all, you're likely the only one selling it, or one of very few people.  At higher levels, 10k plat is some good money, but not terrible to obtain.  Some camping, some farming, and you have it.  Sometimes much better than risking your life in a hard hard place to get something you could buy.<BR>
<BR>
Face it... with rare or very high level items, it is very heavily a seller's market.  If it isn't worth it to you, don't send an offer that's 10% of the asking price... because someone out there most likely WILL buy it at the asked price if it's very rare because they really really want it and they're high enough level to afford it.<BR>
<BR>
Statmongers beware.  Getting 80% to an "optimal" set of equipment is easy.  But... that last 20% is expensive!  (Is it worth it?  Hehe yes indeed it is!  That extra 200-400 mana or so can save your LIFE in a pinch!)</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
